  CFP: MIRAGE 2007 - Lecture Notes in Computer Science
  Dan.Popescu@cmis.csiro.au

CALL FOR PAPERS MIRAGE 2007 - Lecture Notes in Computer Science.

November 1, 2006:  Full paper submission deadline

Mirage 2007 is an international conference with focus on Computer
Vision/Computer Graphics collaboration techniques involving image
analysis/synthesis approaches. In the domain of Computer Vision, this
analysis by synthesis collaboration may take the form of model-based
approaches for which the analysis, recognition or understanding process
does not rely on the data only but is linked to
the optimization of a parametric model introduced A PRIORI.
In the field of Computer Graphics, this thematic refers to image-based
approaches which found the modeling, animation, lighting or rendering
process on the analysis of real pre-existing data in order to
gain in productivity or in realism ...

For more details, see: http://acivs.org/mirage2007/

