  rkowalczyk@ict.cwin.edu.au

TWO RESEARCH POSITIONS IN INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY

The Centre for Information Technology Research (CITR) at Swinburne
University of Technology, Melbourne, Australia, is seeking to appoint
2 research academics in the strategic research themes of the Centre.

The Centre for Information Technology Research (CITR) was formed in 2005
within the Faculty of Information and Communication Technologies as the
University's locus for research in computer science, software engineering
and information systems. CITR carries out research in close collaboration
with industry and research partners nationally and internationally,
supported by a wide range of research grants, strategic partnership
arrangements and industrial R&D projects. With some 70 research staff and
postgraduate research students, and a substantial portfolio of aligned
research activities CITR is emerging as one of the fastest growing and
most concentrated IT research centres in Australia.

The Centre undertakes fundamental and applied research across its
constituent areas contributing to two major research themes of Reliable
Software Systems and Service Oriented Computing. It embraces research in
Complex Intelligent Systems, Component Software and Enterprise Systems, ..... 
http://www.it.usyd.edu.au/~it-announce/news.htm#jobad.txt1

