  Engineering-appoint@vuw.ac.nz

Victoria University of Wellington is introducing a new Bachelor of
Engineering with a specialisation in Software Engineering. The University
is seeking an individual with demonstrated evidence of leadership in
research and teaching in the broad areas of software engineering, formal
systems, or human computer interaction. The appointee will be expected
to take a lead role in the development of the software engineering
specialisation, to develop a personal research programme and to contribute
to the teaching programme of the intended Faculty of Engineering.

The new Bachelor of Engineering is focused on the broad information and
communications technology sector with specialisations in electronic
engineering, computer system engineering, and network engineering in
addition to software engineering. The engineering faculty consists of
approximately a dozen existing staff drawn from computer science and
electronics, all with an engineering background or focus. The University
is committed to the development of an internationally recognised
engineering programme.

