  Lecturer in Software Engineering, Victoria University of Wellington
  Engineering-appoint@vuw.ac.nz

Faculty of Engineering

Victoria University of Wellington is introducing a new Bachelor of
Engineering with a specialisation in Software Engineering. The University
is seeking an individual with research and teaching interests in the
broad areas of software engineering, formal methods, or human computer
interaction. The appointee will be expected to participate in the
development of the software engineering specialisation, to develop a
personal research programme and to contribute to the teaching programme
of the intended Faculty of Engineering.

The new Bachelor of Engineering is focused on the broad information and
communications technology sector with specialisations in electronic
engineering, computer system engineering, and network engineering in
addition to software engineering. The engineering faculty consists of
approximately a dozen existing staff drawn from computer science and
electronics, all with an engineering background or focus. The University
is committed to the development of an internationally recognised
engineering programme.

Applications close Friday 10 November 2006. ..... 
http://www.it.usyd.edu.au/~it-announce/news.htm#jobad.txt6

======================================================================

  Senior Lecturer/Associate Professor in Electronics or Computer Systems Engineering
  Engineering-appoint@vuw.ac.nz

Victoria University of Wellington is introducing a new Bachelor of
Engineering with a specialisation in Computer Systems Engineering. The
University is seeking to appoint up to two senior staff with demonstrated
evidence of leadership in research and teaching in the general areas
of electronics and/or computer systems engineering. The appointee(s)
will be expected to have a significant role in the development of the
electronics and computer systems engineering specialisations, to develop
a personal research programme and to contribute to the teaching programme
of the intended Faculty of Engineering. This is a unique opportunity to
influence the development of an exciting new degree programme.

The new Bachelor of Engineering offers specialisations in electronic
engineering, computer system engineering, network engineering and software
engineering. The current engineering faculty consists of approximately
a dozen existing staff drawn from computer science and electronics,
all with an engineering background or focus. It is anticipated that the
academic and technical staff in engineering will grow significantly in
the next three years. The University is committed to the development of
an internationally recognised engineering programme.

Applications close Friday 10 November 2006. ..... 
http://www.it.usyd.edu.au/~it-announce/news.htm#jobad.txt7

